current.shipping_tab_content:
Returns Policy

You may return most new, unopened items within 30 days of delivery for a full refund. We'll also pay the return shipping costs if the return is a result of our error (you received an incorrect or defective item, etc.).

You should expect to receive your refund within four weeks of giving your package to the return shipper, however, in many cases you will receive a refund more quickly. This time period includes the transit time for us to receive your return from the shipper (5 to 10 business days), the time it takes us to process your return once we receive it (3 to 5 business days), and the time it takes your bank to process our refund request (5 to 10 business days).

If you need to return an item, simply login to your account, view the order using the 'Complete Orders' link under the My Account menu and click the Return Item(s) button. We'll notify you via e-mail of your refund once we've received and processed the returned item.

Shipping

We can ship to virtually any address in the world. Note that there are restrictions on some products, and some products cannot be shipped to international destinations.

When you place an order, we will estimate shipping and delivery dates for you based on the availability of your items and the shipping options you choose. Depending on the shipping provider you choose, shipping date estimates may appear on the shipping quotes page.

settings.cb_content_banner1: In its most basic farm, tonic water is a carbonated drink that contains sugar, flavours and quinine. More premium versions, such as StrangeLove Tonic Water, also contain complex and diverse botanicals that are added to the tonic to make it better suited to specific styles of gin. With so many different new-wave gins on the market, tonics are following suit, with interesting and eclectic flavours and unique production mothods. StrangeLove Dirty Tonic, for example, contains over seven different, distinct botanicals including rosemary, sea salt, lemon oils and orange peel.
settings.cb_title_banner2: Bitter Lemon Tonic: How to Pair
settings.cb_content_banner2: BItter Lemon is traditionally served with Fruit-infused or Sloe Gins on account of it's high citrus content. Having more acidity allows this tonic to cut through the sweetness of such gins, adding an acid profile that makes for a perfectly-balanced and well-rounded end product. One extremely popular use of our Bitter Lemon Tonic Water has been with the Bloody Shiraz Gin by Victorian Distillery Four Pillars.

settings.cb_content_banner1:
Yuzu is a hybrid citrus thought to have originated in China as a cross between a Mandarin Orange and a Ichang Papeda (another exotic citrus variety).

Unlike most citrus, it a Yuzu tree can tolerate frost, so is often grown in cooler climates. It has become somewhat of a staple of Japanese cuisine where it is used as a seasoning for sashimi, in sauces, as a dressing and also as a flavouring for beverages.
settings.cb_content_banner2: Really Yuzu tastes like a combination of a mandarin, lemon, grapefruit and pomelo. Basically it tastes like the best citrus you've ever had. Though not abundant in juice, it makes up for it with both the depth and complexity of flavour. This makes it perfect as a beverage ingredient and for use in mixing - a personal favourite here is to use as a mixer in a Sake Yuzu Highball - staying true Yuzu's popularity in Japan.

settings.b_bv1_content: Our mixed packs of Premium Mixers and Lo-Cal Sodas span the best of our collection - from Ginger Beer to Yuzu to Tonic Water. Conveniently curated so you can spend less time deciding and more time making gin & tonics.

Founded in Byron Bay in 2012, we have grown from one organic Ginger Beer product to over 20 unique and eclectic products spanning Premium Mixers, Lo-Cal Sodas and Mineral Water. We are commited to supporting Australian producers, over 97% of our ingredients are sourced locally.

Check out our range of curated
cocktails and brand collaborations
including Gin & Tonic, Dark & Stormy
and Paloma recipes that will make your mouth water.

Cocktails delivered Australia Wide.

Whether mixing cocktails - or simple built drinks at home - our award-winning range of premium mixers and tonic water uses the finest Australian ingredients to deliver a perfect pairing for any spirit - gin, tequila, mezcal, rum or whisky.

The easiest way to explain the difference between ginger ale and ginger beer is that, traditionally, ginger ales use a ginger extract or flavour to impart flavour, while ginger beer uses ginger juice that is brewed. Flavour wise, ginger ales and more delicate and lightly flavoured than a brewed ginger drink.

Our ginger beers are made using the finest Buderim Ginger Juice from Queensland. We brew in a tank for several days with Fijian ginger root and - in the case of our mixer product - add a lick of Sichuan Pepper for even more spice.
